<h2><span class="title" 
    >OneTime &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp; Encryption with One-Time Pads</span></h2>

<h4><p class="notice" >Update (2016-10-29): OneTime 2.0 is currently in
beta testing.  The latest version is <a href="onetime-2XVERSION"
>2XVERSION</a>&nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;please give it a try and
<a href="https://github.com/kfogel/OneTime/issues/new" >report</a>
any bugs you find.  See the <a href="changes" >release notes</a>
for details about what's new in 2.0.</p></h4>

<div class="row">

  <div class="four column" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1em;">
    <a href="get" ><img src="images/logo/onetime-logo-color-225x225.png" alt="OneTime logo" /></a>
  </div>

  <div class="four column">
    <p><a href="onetime">OneTime</a> is an <a href="LICENSE" >open
    source</a> encryption program that uses
    the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One-time_pad">one-time
    pad</a> algorithm to allow two parties to communicate privately.
    It has features to assist with pad management, and comes with
    built-in <a href="#help" >help</a>.</p>

    <p>OneTime is for users who are comfortable with command-line
    programs.  It requires Python 2.6 or higher, but has not been
    ported to Python 3 (there's
    an <a href="https://github.com/kfogel/OneTime/issues/15" >open
    ticket</a> for that and patches are welcome).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="four column">
